latestPosts.caption:
A Day to Remember! 🚀

Yesterday, we had the incredible opportunity to meet @peyushbansal , and it was truly a once-in-a-lifetime experience. The last 24 hours were filled with anxiety and pressure — not because of data or numbers, but because of that one defining moment when Peyush Sir will walk in and say, “Hi Aarjav, how are you?” I had no idea how would I react, but when it finally happened, it became one of the best moments of my life.

Our meeting revolved around, how we can optimize performance through ad account structuring and content strategies on Lenskart. It was an intense yet rewarding discussion.

I have been watching Shark Tank India for the past four years, Peyush Sir has always been the entrepreneur, I admire the most. His vision, humility, and approach to entrepreneurship are truly inspiring. Thank you, Peyush Sir, for this amazing opportunity—I look forward to growing this partnership and making waves in the D2C space!

A huge shoutout to our early brands and team members who believed in us even when we were just getting started. Your trust and support means everything.

Big goals ahead—₹1000 Cr in monthly revenue in D2C space is on the way! 💪🔥

“Learn D2C with Aarjav” course is live!

The idea behind the course is to make sure that every Brand owner, Marketer has a good idea how digital marketing works in D2C space.

When we take interviews of the marketers and talk to brand owners during onboarding, we realise there was a lack of knowledge and direction of working was not right.

We have been running a D2C marketing agency @digisidekick for the last 3 years and we have grown more than 20 brands from 0 to 1Cr. Per month sales.

One thing that was common amongst these 20 brands is the knowledge the brand owner holds around D2C.

The objective of the course is to make sure that you as an individual know how to scale your D2C brand by your own.

Online buying in India is only 7% today which will be 40% in the coming 5 years, so be the part of the journey.

If you are a marketer, aspiring D2C Brand owner or want a career switch then this is a perfect choice for you as every chapter will focus around D2C digital marketing not general Digital Marketing.

🔴👇 HERE IS THE AI PROMPT WE USED TO GENERATE THE IMAGES 👇🔴
.
.
📌 Step 1: Find a visual reference that matches the vibe you want (lighting, setting, model pose, styling)

Ideal sources: Pinterest, Instagram, past shoots

📌 Step 2: Upload the image to Chat GPT and ask it to share a Sora Prompt based on this template:

[Create a cinematic, moody nightclub scene featuring a stylish male model with long hair and a beard, wearing the given shirt. The model is mid-dance with a confident, relaxed expression.

Setting: Indoors at a premium nightclub or lounge with intense colored lighting. The background should include a red smoke effect, ambient purple and green lights, and a blurred crowd to evoke a lively nightlife atmosphere.

Lighting: Low-key, colored lighting with a deep red and magenta glow on one side of the subject and subtle highlights on the hair. Include light reflecting off the shirt for added depth and texture.

Mood: Cool, unapologetically confident, party-animal energy. The subject is the center of attention, standing tall and owning the vibe.

Composition: Slightly low angle shot for a powerful look. Include a soft background bokeh with colorful club lights and vague silhouettes of people dancing.

Style: Modern club fashion with a slightly rebellious undertone. Perfect for luxury partywear or nightlife fashion campaigns.]

📌 Step 3: Upload the prompt to Sora along with your product images and see the magic begin
.
.
.
.

If there’s one thing I’ve truly learned in my last 4 years of entrepreneurship — it’s PERSEVERANCE!
.
.
In the first two years alone, I registered 7 different companies. Today, only one of them stands tall: DigiSidekick. The rest? Shut down

It’s not that I lacked the capability or resources to run those businesses. What I lacked was PERSEVERANCE — the patience to stick through the slow growth, the messy middle, and the uncomfortable unknowns

Because building something like Infosys doesn’t happen overnight. It takes 40 years of relentless effort

So I’ve made a decision — I’m giving the next 40 years of my life to DigiSidekick!

This is my tapas,
This is what PERSEVERANCE means to me!
.
.
Until next time
Happy Marketing 💪

Due to some technical glich the pinned comment is not shown to everyone so here it is:

Prompt:

You're a professional ad scriptwriter who specializes in viral, high-performing Facebook video ads. I want you to write a script that:

Hooks the audience in the first 3 seconds

Clearly showcases the product/service

Builds an emotional or rational reason to care

Ends with a powerful CTA

Follows the ideal format for a short Facebook ad (30–60 seconds max)

Sounds natural when spoken in a [Language: Hindi / Hinglish / English]

Here are the details:

Product / Service / Event Name: [Insert here]
What It Does: [Briefly explain the core offering or use-case]
Target Audience: [Who are we talking to? e.g. Gen Z men, new moms, startup founders]
Tone: [Witty / Emotional / Urgent / Luxury / Mass appeal / Youthful etc.]
Key Features / Benefits: [Add USPs or product highlights]
Offer (if any): [Mention discounts, deadlines, limited edition etc.]
Call to Action: [e.g., Shop Now, Download, DM us, Visit Website]

Please include:

A scroll-stopping hook in the first line

Conversational tone with natural pauses

Clear visual cues or scene suggestions for video editors

Optionally add a voiceover tone suggestion (e.g. dramatic, fun, fast-paced)
.
.
.
